==English==

===Etymology===
From the slang expression "Having one's head up one's ass," thus, wearing the ass as a hat.

The term is applied to people who are clueless or bumbling, who don't understand what is going on.

Also- when used by Gordon Highlander, means 'a person much liked and loved by all society, such as T52'

